{"title":"Updated Allied ABLE Gravel Bike Takes Big Tires & Speed Seriously","link":"https://bikerumor.com/updated-allied-able-gravel-bike/","date":1744120800000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-tire--1536x1025.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1025\" alt=\"Allied ABLE Gravel Bike teaser tire\" /></p>\n<p>Allied Cycle Works pulled the wraps off the next-generation ABLE gravel bike, their modern gravel speed machine. Narrow where it needs to be, aero shaping, and fits up to 57mm (2.3″) tires. It hits all the in-vogue gravel hotness. Allied says this isn’t just a refresh—it’s a ground-up redesign.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-2--jpg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"8023\" height=\"5351\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-2--jpg.webp\" alt=\"Allied ABLE Gravel Bike teaser 2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-2--jpg.webp 8023w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-2--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-2--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-2--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-2--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-2--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-2--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos: Allied)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Aimed at tackling today’s fastest, roughest courses with more speed, capability, and versatility than ever before. Available as a frameset or in three top-tier (SRAM) builds, the new ABLE is built for riders who are serious about their gravel fun.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-front--jpg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"8035\" height=\"5359\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-front--jpg.webp\" alt=\"Allied ABLE Gravel Bike teaser front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-front--jpg.webp 8035w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-front--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-front--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-front--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-front--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-front--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser-front--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Built for Speed, Tuned for the Rough Stuff</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Gravel racing isn’t what it was a few years ago—it’s faster, more tactical, and much wider. Allied leaned into that reality and gave the ABLE the tools to handle it. The redesigned frame sheds weight while still delivering the stiffness and compliance needed to hammer over everything from smooth dirt roads to brutal rock gardens. With clearance for up to 57mm tires, it’s got the footprint to handle anything a race throws at it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser--scaled.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1750\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Allied ABLE Gravel Bike teaser\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser--297x203.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser--1536x1050.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser--120x82.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser--768x525.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-teaser--2048x1400.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>One of the biggest upgrades? </em></strong>Geometry tweaks that improve high-speed stability while keeping that razor-sharp agility for tight, technical terrain. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-geo-.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2688\" height=\"1498\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-geo-.png\" alt=\"Allied ABLE geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-geo-.png 2688w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-geo--297x166.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-geo--1536x856.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-geo--120x67.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-geo--768x428.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-geo--2048x1141.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Add in fully internal cable routing and <a href=\"https://alliedcycleworks.com/products/allied-echo-stem?srsltid=AfmBOootBtzouMceNwaEoVFIj4GGzOkJTYg0TwlDt5mj_IAmzero8YKe\">Allied’s ST03 adjustable stem </a>(I know, sounds crazy, it’s super cool), letting riders switch between two rise options without re-cabling—and you’ve got a sleek, clean cockpit built for business.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-seat-tube--jpg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"8023\" height=\"5351\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-seat-tube--jpg.webp\" alt=\"Allied ABLE Gravel Bike force Mulle seat tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-seat-tube--jpg.webp 8023w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-seat-tube--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-seat-tube--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-seat-tube--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-seat-tube--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-seat-tube--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-seat-tube--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Smart Storage, No Compromises</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Gravel racing is as much about efficiency as power, and Allied didn’t overlook the small stuff. The ABLE debuts a new magnetic-latching internal storage compartment that saves weight over traditional under-the-bottle designs while keeping bottle mounts secure. It’s clean, practical, and keeps your essentials out of the elements without compromising bottle placement.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet--jpg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"8023\" height=\"5351\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet--jpg.webp\" alt=\"Allied ABLE Gravel Bike force Mullet\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet--jpg.webp 8023w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Allied ABLE <strong>Build Options</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>SRAM RED XPLR AXS:</strong> This is a no-compromise race machine. Wireless electronic shifting, Industry Nine SOLIX SL AR40c carbon wheels, and a sub-16.3lb build make this the lightest and fastest setup.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SRAM FORCE AXS MULLET:</strong> A 1x drivetrain paired with a wide-range mountain cassette and Industry Nine 1/1 Ultralite Carbon Gravel wheels. </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SRAM RIVAL AXS MULLET:</strong> Bringing wireless shifting to a more accessible price point, the Rival AXS build delivers top-tier performance without breaking the bank.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>ABLE FRAMESET:</strong> This includes Allied’s carbon frame, the ST03 stem/headset, and the SP02 seat post with independent fore/aft saddle adjustments—perfect for riders who want to spec their dream build.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-front--jpg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"8023\" height=\"5351\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-front--jpg.webp\" alt=\"Allied ABLE Gravel Bike force Mulle front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-front--jpg.webp 8023w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-front--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-front--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-front--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-front--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-front--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mulle-front--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Finished In the USA</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You might remember from our<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/allied-adjustable-duet-cockpit-system-bc40-kate-courtney/\"> Updated: BC-40 piece with Kate Courtney </a><span><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/allied-adjustable-duet-cockpit-system-bc40-kate-courtney/\" target=\"_blank\">from a while back, </a>Allied recently moved its carbon production offsite. This means that each ABLE frame is finished in Bentonville, Arkansas, but not hand-made there like the previous model. However, ALLIED still designs, prototypes, paints, and hand-assembles all its</span> bikes at the factory in Bentonville.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet-side--jpg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"8023\" height=\"5351\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet-side--jpg.webp\" alt=\"Allied ABLE Gravel Bike force Mullet side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet-side--jpg.webp 8023w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet-side--297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet-side--1536x1024.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet-side--120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet-side--768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet-side--800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Allied-ABLE-Gravel-Bike-force-Mullet-side--720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><br />Allied ABLE Availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The new ABLE will be available for order starting April 8, 2025, through ALLIED’s website and select retailers. The MSRP of the new ABLE frameset with stem and seat post starts at $4,000. For more information, visit <a href=\"https://alliedcycleworks.com/collections/able\">alliedcycleworks.com.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/updated-allied-able-gravel-bike/\">Updated Allied ABLE Gravel Bike Takes Big Tires &amp; Speed Seriously</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"fecdef34af4674abbff62e8b981801f13fc361a0ca81306b93bfa8c627006ed4","category":"Cycling"}